2. Why Python? (Need for Python in Industry)
The trainer explains that there are multiple programming languages, but Python is preferred because:
Python is an interpreter-dependent language
Interpreter-based languages are best suited for scripting
Scripting means writing small test cases or snippets to:
Test application functionality
Perform integration testing
Validate deployments
Use in Industry:
DevOps engineers
Cloud engineers
Developers
Integration and deployment teams
All these roles increasingly require basic scripting skills, and Python is the most commonly used language for this purpose.
3. What is Scripting?
Scripting refers to writing small, executable programs (test cases/snippets) to:
Test specific features of an application
Validate deployment steps
Perform automation tasks
Not all languages support scripting efficiently.
Examples:
âŒ C language â†’ Compiler-dependent â†’ Not suitable for scripting
âœ… Python, JavaScript, Java â†’ Interpreter-based â†’ Suitable for scripting
4. Compiler vs Interpreter (Core Concept)
Both compiler and interpreter are translators that convert:
Source code â†’ Machine code (binary)
Because computers only understand binary (0s and 1s).
ğŸ”¹ Compiler Characteristics
Translates the entire program at once
Converts code block by block
Displays all errors together after compilation
Program does not execute until all errors are fixed
Example language: C
Illustration used:
A C program with multiple errors shows all errors at once during compilation.
ğŸ”¹ Interpreter Characteristics
Translates line by line
Executes one line at a time
Stops immediately at the first error
Does not proceed until the error is fixed
Example language: Python
Illustration used:
A Python program with errors stops execution at the first faulty line and reports only that error.
ğŸ”‘ Key Difference Summary
Compiler
Interpreter
Converts entire code
Converts line by line
Shows all errors together
Shows errors one at a time
Faster execution
Slower but more precise
Not ideal for testing
Ideal for scripting & testing
5. Why Interpreter Languages Are Preferred for Testing
Testing is sensitive and precise
Interpreter checks each line carefully
Errors are detected immediately
Ensures correctness before moving forward
Hence, interpreter-dependent languages like Python are best for scripting and testing.
6. Prerequisites to Learn Python
No prerequisites required
Even beginners or school-level learners can start
No prior knowledge of C, Java, or any language needed
Python syntax is simple and readable
This makes Python ideal as a first programming language.
7. Python as a High-Level & General-Purpose Language
ğŸ”¹ High-Level Language
Python uses:
English-like words (if, else, print)
Simple mathematical expressions
Easy-to-read syntax
This makes Python human-readable and user-friendly.
ğŸ”¹ General-Purpose Language
Python can be used to develop:
Web applications
Desktop applications
Mobile applications
Embedded systems
Database applications
Automation and testing scripts
Thus, Python is called a general-purpose programming language.
8. Key Features of Python
1. Interpreter-Dependent
Executes code line by line
Best suited for scripting and testing
2. Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)
Supports:
Encapsulation
Abstraction
Inheritance
Polymorphism
3. General-Purpose
Can be used across domains and platforms.
4. Dynamically Typed Language
No need to declare data types explicitly
Python automatically detects the type at runtime
Example:
Copy code
Python
a = 10
print(type(a))
Python identifies a as an integer automatically.
